	<p>This is some sample text.</p>
</main>

<!-- Footer section -->
<footer>
	<p>&copy; 2023 My Website</p>
</footer>
```
Semantic HTML elements help search engines and screen readers understand the structure of your content, making it more accessible and easier to maintain.

**Step 4: Style Your Website with CSS**

Create a new file called `style.css` and add your CSS styles:
```css
body {
	background-color: #f2f2f2;
	font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
}

header {
	background-color: #333;
	color: #fff;
	padding: 20px;
	text-align: center;
}

