nav.style.display = 'none';

// Add an event listener to the hamburger icon
const hamburger = document.querySelector('.hamburger');
hamburger.addEventListener('click', () => {
  nav.style.display = 'block';
});
```
**Step 6: Test and Refine**

Test your website in a web browser to ensure it looks and works as expected. Refine your HTML, CSS, and JavaScript code as needed to fix any issues or improve the user experience.

That's it! You've created a basic website using HTML, CSS, and (optional) JavaScript from scratch. Of course, this is just the beginning, and there's much more to learn about web development. Keep practicing and experimenting to improve your skills.

